11:
Phew! The Kaleidoscope's no walk in
the park once you get to the lower
levels.
15:
Agreed. Let us head back up after a
moment of respite—
27: Are you okay there? Wait... Pecorine?
29:
Huh? Oh, it's you guys from the other
day...
34:
Are you hurt? Did the monsters give
you a hard time?
39:
I don't see any injuries... Oh
no—you're not poisoned, are you?!
44:
Nuh-uh... I can't move because... I'm
running on an empty stomach...
49:
An empty stomach, huh? We need
to get you treated right away—
59:
Mm, I can already feel the nutrition
flowing into every part of my body!
A nice picnic like this is just what I
needed!
61:
The best part was the chef's
attention to nutritional balance.
64:
Did you make all this food, Alk? How
crazy is that?!
68:
Yes. Alk's culinary skills are
top-notch. Though I do not find that
to be crazy.
73:
Ahaha... Now you're making me
blush.
78:
For you to brave the Kaleidoscope
alone must mean you've taken on
the role of adventurer.
82:
Mm-hm. I figured I have to make
ends meet first before I can even
figure out how to get back home.
85:
But to explore these ruins until
you've collapsed of hunger is surely
a bit extreme. How long have you
been at it?
88:
Only half a day actually. I guess I'm
not exactly the most
energy-efficient adventurer. I go
hungry sooo fast.
94: Energy efficiency? Is that a thing?
97:
But thanks to your food, Alk, I'm
feeling so much better now! I owe
you one!
107:
I have to say, I sure wasn't expecting
to bump into you guys in the
Kaleidoscope.
110:
We were just as surprised. It's a
good thing we met here though. I'm
sure Light would agree.
116:
I missed my chance to bring this up
during our last encounter, but...
117: We may be able to help you.
118: I wanted you to know that.
123:
You mean... you might be able to
help me get back to my world?
129:
How did you come to that
conclusion?
132:
The taste of Alk's cooking was
distinctly different from the typical
fare you find in this world—it felt
much more culturally varied.
134:
It got me wondering if you might've
drifted here like us.
136:
Except the ingredients, seasoning,
and taste all seemed remarkably
fresh from what I could tell.
137:
I figured you must have some way
of transporting things from other
worlds into this one.
139:
At least that's what my gut tells me.
So? Am I right?
150:
It's definitely crazy how you can
figure out so much just from eating
one of my packed lunches...
154:
Ehehe. I'll have you know I'm not a
gourmet for nothing!
159:
Impressive. That'll make explaining
things much easier. The truth is...
163:
The World Flipper?! That sounds
really handy...
166:
I bet you could use it to munch on
the food of every world out there!
How crazy is that?!
171:
I mean, we have our own travels to
worry about, so it's not like we can
take you around for food all the
time, but we can at least help you
get back.
173: Of course, it's entirely up to you.
178:
My answer's a resounding YES! In
fact, I can't thank you enough for
going out of your way to—
190:
You guys watch—I'll show you just
what I'm capable of!
211:
Ehehe... Consider it my way of
saying thanks for the lunch.
216:
It sure is a relief knowing you can
take care of yourself. Welcome
aboard.
